parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end shimmy/wobble can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes or wobbles violently
often triggered by hitting a bump or pothole in the road
and can be accompanied by a loss of steering control
swerving
or vibration in the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The power steering system fails
causing the steering wheel to become difficult to turn
or the vehicle to pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end shimmy/vibration can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes or vibrates violently when hitting a bump or uneven road surface
the steering wheel shakes
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle may swerve into another lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
smoke billows out of the exhaust
the warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle vibrates excessively
and the turbocharger fails to provide adequate boost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR cooler can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the EGR valve warning light illuminates
the coolant leaks
and the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
or experiences difficulty starting
and the fuel pump or injectors fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch fan can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage or failure.
symptoms: The clutch fan fails to shut off
causing the engine to overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the acceleration system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
loses power
or experiences difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the fuel tank and contamination of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and shut down while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
or shuts down while driving
often without warning; the engine filter gets clogged
causing the truck to run erratically and stall; the fuel tank liner is rusted
and the fuel filter and fuel lines become clogged; the vehicle has difficulty starting or runs rough; the engine stutter or completely shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and shut down while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
or shuts down while driving
often without warning; the engine filter gets clogged
causing the truck to run erratically and stall; the fuel injectors break or become damaged
causing the engine to run rough or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stutter or shut off can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shut down while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stutter or completely shuts off while driving; the vehicle has difficulty starting or runs rough; the fuel tank liner is rusted
and the fuel filter and fuel lines become clogged.
